By Hussaini Hammangabdo, The Adamawa state police Command has lauded RoLAC, British Council and EU for providing American standard Statement Taking Room (STR) for its personnel at Criminal Investigation Department, the highest investigative body in the Command. DSP Sulaiman Yahaya PPRO of the command said, the statement taking room (STR) is the first of its kind in the northeast region . RoLAC in collaboration with the British Council and European Union provided an equipped statement taking room for the Command and family support unit kids in Doubeli, Ganye and Numan Divisions. Recorded  investigations by the police will not only going to enhance professionalism and effectiveness but will  curb out the lost and change of suspect’s statement in court/ custody. The visionary  RoLAC coordinator, Barrister Hafsatu Abdullahi, who made the presentation to Commissioner of police added that utilizing the STR will reduce the length of time occasioned during criminal trials and ultimately contribute to speedy dispensation of justice. The Chief justice of Adamawa state represented by High court judge, Justice Abdulazees Waziri equally advice the command to train their officers to judiciously use the equipment for effective service delivery. The command expressed gratitude to the entire body of RoLAC, United Nation and European Union for the gesture. 